---
import "@/styles/global.css";
import BaseLayout from "@/components/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  SEOTitle="Large Language Models | PrincipalAI"
  SEODescription="Large language model systems for evidence retrieval, analysis, reporting, and decision support."
>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#071f3f] via-[#123f86] to-[#e8f4ff] px-8 py-24 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-blue-100">
        Large Language Models
      </p>

      <h1 class="max-w-5xl font-serif text-5xl font-bold leading-tight sm:text-6xl">
        Language models built around evidence, context, and decisions.
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-relaxed text-blue-50">
        PrincipalAI applies large language models to professional workflows where information retrieval, synthesis, analysis, and judgement matter.
      </p>

      <a href="/contact" class="mt-8 inline-block rounded-md bg-blue-600 px-7 py-3 font-semibold text-white hover:bg-blue-700">
        Request a demonstration
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main>
    <section class="bg-white px-8 py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-blue-600">The problem</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-gray-900">
            Generic AI is not enough for professional decision-making.
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
          <p>
            Large language models can summarise, classify, draft, and reason across complex information. But professional use requires more than a general-purpose chatbot.
          </p>
          <p>
            Organisations need systems that connect language models to approved knowledge sources, controlled workflows, domain expertise, and human review.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-gray-50 px-8 py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-blue-600">What it supports</p>
        <h2 class="max-w-4xl font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-gray-900">
          Language models applied to evidence-heavy work.
        </h2>

        <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
          <div class="rounded-md bg-white p-7 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Evidence retrieval</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
              Help users find relevant material across reports, research, data sources, and organisational knowledge.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-md bg-white p-7 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Synthesis</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
              Compare sources, extract findings, summarise evidence, and identify areas of agreement or uncertainty.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-md bg-white p-7 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Analytical drafting</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
              Support reports, policy advice, business cases, technical notes, and decision papers.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-md bg-white p-7 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Review support</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
              Assist with consistency checks, evidence tracing, assumptions review, and structured quality assurance.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-white px-8 py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-blue-600">Why PrincipalAI</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-gray-900">
            LLMs connected to real analytical systems.
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
          <p>
            PrincipalAI does not treat language models as standalone tools. We connect them to documents, models, datasets, workflows, dashboards, and expert review.
          </p>
          <p>
            This allows organisations to use LLMs in ways that support productivity while preserving context, evidence, and professional judgement.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-[#071f3f] px-8 py-20 text-white">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl text-center">
        <h2 class="mx-auto max-w-4xl font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight">
          Apply language models where evidence and judgement matter.
        </h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-blue-50">
          Talk to PrincipalAI about LLM systems for research, policy, technical advisory, and organisational knowledge.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="mt-8 inline-block rounded-md bg-blue-600 px-7 py-3 font-semibold text-white hover:bg-blue-700">
          Request a demonstration
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
